#: core/text_manager/texts.py:170
msgid ""
"<b>👨‍💻 Admin Panel</b>\n"
"   -> <b>🛒 Order Management</b>\n"
"\n"
"🔸 Click on a status to toggle the display of orders with that specific "
"status.\n"
"\n"
"🔸 Enter a user_id in the format <b>'id-********'</b> to set a filter by"
" User ID.\n"
"🔸 Enter an order_id in the format <b>'o_id-********'</b> to set a filter"
" by Order ID.\n"
"🔸 Enter an order target link in the format <b>'link-********'</b> to "
"set a filter by link.\n"
"\n"
"🔸 Current filter settings:\n"
"   ▫️ id: {user_id}\n"
"   ▫️ order_id: {order_id}\n"
"   ▫️ link: {link}\n"
"   ▫️ Statuses:\n"
msgstr ""

#: core/text_manager/texts.py:196
msgid ""
"<b>🛒 My Orders</b>\n"
"\n"
"Here, all your orders are grouped into 3 categories based on their status:\n"
"\n"
"🟢 <b>Active -</b> {pending} | {new} | {in_progress}\n"
"\n"
"✅ <b>Completed -</b> {completed} | {partial}\n"
"\n"
"❌ <b>Canceled -</b> {canceled}\n"
"\n"
"You can toggle the display of these groups by clicking the "
"corresponding button.\n"
"Alternatively, click the <b>🛒 All Orders</b> button to display everything."
msgstr ""

